 'UK travellers visiting Indonesia, including Bali, normally need a visa on arrival (VOA) for tourism, and can either buy it at the airport or arrange an electronic e-VOA online before departure. Both cover a short tourist stay and can usually be extended once. We are an independent service that helps you prepare the e-VOA — not a government website, and our service fee is separate from the official VOA fee.',
