 '<h2>What it is</h2><p>The Canada eTA is required for visa-exempt nationals, including British citizens, arriving by air; it is generally not needed for entry by land or sea. It is electronically linked to the passport you apply with and is typically valid for up to five years or until that passport expires, allowing multiple short visits. It does not guarantee entry — the final decision rests with a border officer.</p><h2>How to apply</h2><p>Apply on the official Government of Canada eTA site: enter your passport, contact and travel details, answer the eligibility questions and pay. Many approvals come within minutes, but some take longer if a review is needed, so apply before you book non-refundable travel. An express tier with us speeds up <em>our</em> handling only — it cannot make Canada decide faster or guarantee approval.</p><h3>FAQ</h3><p><strong>Is it a visa?</strong> No — it is an authorisation tied to your passport. <strong>How long valid?</strong> Up to five years or passport expiry. <strong>Needed for driving across the border?</strong> Generally only required for air travel.</p>',
